reviewText: Another great Tim Hawkins DVD. New jokes and good clean fun. Not much more need be said. There is always Bill Cosby, Tim Allen, Steve Allen, Tom Arnold, George Carlin, Etc. George Carlin was a bit rough with comedy. Tim Allen is into slap stick. ETC. Sometimes it is good to have good clean comedy.

reviewText: Mr. Hawkins returns with more wit and music, and keeps attention throughout the concert. Thank goodness for the pause button. His accents are well faked, and his mastery of guitar his astounding. Even the comedy is good. (Mind you, that's all I really ask of a comedian, but he blows it out of the water.)

reviewText: Our Pastor showed us this DVD of Tim Hawkins at last night's mid-week service. Said we all need a good laugh and believe me....I've never laughed so hard and for so long !! Tim Hawkins is fantastic. What a talented singer as well as comedian. So refreshing to find a comedian who's clean...no swear words...and just plain funny.  Had to get my own copy to enjoy whenever I want a good laugh.

reviewText: I've never heard of Tim Hawkins and after a recommendation from a friend, we watched this video of Tim Hawkins over the holidays and we never laughed so hard!  It was so hilarious, I had tears running.  And the nice thing, like some other reviewers have said, it's good, clean humor and just proves that you don't need trash to be funny.  We thoroughly enjoyed this Tim Hawkins video "I'm No Rockstar", and we can't wait to view his other works as well.  He's received a permanent place in our video collection now and has become one of our new favorite comedians!Funny, funny stuff!
